    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Consider moving this skip into the \"Success\" subtest rather than skipping the entire test. The other subtests (EmptyDirectory, ModulesTooLarge, PackingPrioritizesSmallest, etc.) use in-memory filesystems and don't depend on git line ending conversions or platform-specific filesystem behavior.\n\nThis would preserve test coverage for the module packing logic on Windows:\n\n```suggestion\n\tt.Run(\"Success\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\tt.Parallel()\n\t\tif runtime.GOOS == \"windows\" {\n\t\t\tt.Skip(\"Windows path separators and newline handling make this test unreliable.\")\n\t\t}\n```",
